- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper discusses the development of a deep learning framework for handling large scale machine learning applications, specifically using tree ensembles as building blocks. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper applies the developed framework to the task of automatic detection of cash-out fraud, which falls under the domain of security and fraud detection. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the development of a platform for artificial intelligence and the application of deep learning to solve real-world problems. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper specifically focuses on the development of a distributed version of deep forest, which requires distributed computing and parallel processing. 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper may involve the use of databases to store and manage the large amounts of training data used in the experiments.
